Disgruntled eThekwini Municipal Workers have taken to the streets, demanding that the city meet their wage demands. The municipality recently hired members of the MK Veterans on a higher wage scale. DURBAN - Disgruntled eThekwini Municipal Workers have taken to the streets, demanding that the city meet their wage demands. READ: #TshwaneShutdown march unauthorised: police The workers claim the municipality recently hired members of the MK Veterans on a higher wage scale. The employees are now demanding salary level upgrades equal to those of MK veterans. The workers demonstrated the area outside the Durban City Hall. READ: Alex residents vow to shutdown Sandton Service delivery has come to a halt due to the protests.